# Dash guardrails (AGENTS.md wins on conflict)

- App interpreter: `<C:/path/to/envs/app311/python.exe>`. Never the base/default env.
- THE verify command (identical to the git pre-commit gate):
  `powershell -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File scripts/verify.ps1`
- Reproduce the symptom in the browser BEFORE editing. Check the build stamp
  first -- a stale server makes every edit invisible.
- Done = pasted green verify output from THIS session. Unit tests are not
  proof for front-end behavior bugs.
- One bug per session; one commit per verified (green) change; no bundled diffs.
- Tests/verify sandbox state via `<APP_STATE_DIR>`; never write real saved state.
- Never use `--no-verify` or `SKIP_VERIFY=1`. If verify cannot run, stop and
  report the broken toolchain -- fixing it IS the task.

Full rules: ./AGENTS.md
